      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I don't think it's inconsistent. There is a default max fee that is set in the system, and the user can override it with a fee rate. Forcing the user to guess the size of the transaction in order to hit 1 sat/byte (or whatever they're aiming for) is counterproductive.\r\n\r\nEdit: having a \"default max fee rate\" sounds like a good improvement though, IMO. Not sure what a sane value would be though. And what would the wallet do when the blocks were filling up with higher feerate txs? Capping sounds like a bad idea in general. Throwing an error sounds even worse.",
